sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2017011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Modul of the gRNA testing system created by Valencia UPV 2016 team. This system aims to test the functionality and efficiency of a chosen gRNA to target a particular gene. This system is modular, as the gene inserted can be chosen by the user, only taking into account the required overhangs (5'-AATG-3' and 5'-TTCG-3').
It includes a promoter 35s with a 5' region (BBa_K2017002), 20 nucleotides of the TFL consensus gene of Clemenules (clementine orange), the reporter luciferase with SAGTI linker and the terminator Tnos.
Luciferase is out of its reading frame due to a nucleotide added upstream to the linker, and the initial ATG has been removed. This means that when the luciferase is translated, it will not be functional. To make it functional, it is necessary to make indels in the TFL fragment that put the luciferase in the correct reading frame. These indels can be made using the CRISPR/Cas9 system, which is the aim of this device.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Monica Victoria Gutierrez Salazar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was obtained using GoldenBraid assembly. The Ga20ox consense sequence was obtained with oligonucleotide synthesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is important to notice that this device is modular. To insert the region of the gene of interest, this region must have the overhang 5'-AATG-3' and 5'-TTCG-3'.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2017002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Promoter of cauliflower mosaic virus (CaMV), used for constitutive expression in plants. It is fused with the 5' region of the N. benthamiana polyubiquitin gene, which has a high expression rate. It can enhance the expression of the coding region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Monica Victoria Gutierrez Salazar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It must be taken into consideration that the 5' region will be ligated to the coding region, so the overhang need to be compatible.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2017003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Firefly luciferase protein. It oxidates its substrate luciferin, emitting light during the process. It can act as a reporter protein when used with a promoter. This part is made to be fused to the 3' with other coding sequence, so it includes the SAGTI linker in order to let the luciferase acquire the correct tertiary structure.
The luciferase does not include ATG (Met) to initiate translation, as it needs to be fused to 3' of other coding sequence. The translation must begin in the coding sequence fused to the 3'. The linker includes a random nucleotide in 5', to change the reading frame of the luciferase. That way, it will not be translated unless an indel is produced in the coding region to which the part is fused.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Monica Victoria Gutierrez Salazar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Luciferase was obtained from laboratory stock. The linker was fused with a PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part must be fused to the 3' of other coding sequence. In order to be used in our modular gRNA testing system, it was necessary to remove the ATG (Met codon) to avoid unexpected translation. The translation must begin in the coding sequence fused to the 3'. The linker includes a random nucleotide in 5', to change the reading frame of the luciferase. That way, it will not be translated unless an indel is produced in the coding region to which the part is fused.
